iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Madrid - Spanish police say they have arrested a 43-year-old Egyptian man for allegedly belonging to an international terror organisation.Spain's civil guard says the man was arrested on Saturday in the central town of El Espinar near the city of Segovia. It said an extradition order will be begun to return him to Egypt, whose authorities were seeking his arrest.The civil guard said the suspect had been caught by German authorities during raids to break up a terror cell in Hamburg in 2002, only to later be released.Both German and Egyptian authorities gave their Spanish counterparts information leading to his recapture.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.